</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Vīrya</b> (Sanskrit: विर्या; Pāli: <i>viriya</i>; Tibetan Wylie: <i>brtson 'grus</i>) is a <a href="/wiki/Buddhism" title="Buddhism">Buddhist</a> term commonly translated as "energy", "diligence", "enthusiasm", or "effort". It can be defined as an attitude of gladly engaging in wholesome activities, and it functions to cause one to accomplish wholesome or virtuous actions.</p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
<div id="toctitle">
<h2>Contents</h2>
</div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#Etymology"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Etymology</span></a></li>
